****Interview Pointer of view**********

Definition: “A class is a blueprint for objects that defines attributes and behavior.”

Difference between Class & Object:

Class → Blueprint

Object → Instance of a class

Why use classes?

Code reusability

Encapsulation

Organization of data & behavior

Constructors:

Default constructor → No parameters

Parameterized constructor → Initialize attributes directly





*******simple example **********


public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Car myCar = new Car();    // Object creation
        myCar.color = "Red";
        myCar.model = "Tesla";

        myCar.start();            // Call method
    }
}


Car → class (blueprint)

myCar → object (instance of the class)
